!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

hearty /ˈhɑːtɪ/

(heartier,heartiest) 

1. ADJ Hearty people or actions are loud, cheerful, and energetic. 喧闹活泼的 

例： Wade was a hearty, athletic sort of guy. 韦德是那种精力充沛、身体强壮的家伙。 

2. heartily ADV 喧闹活泼地 [ADV after v] 

例： He laughed heartily. 他开怀大笑。 

3. ADJ Hearty feelings or opinions are strongly felt or strongly held. (感情或观点等) 强烈的 

例： With the last sentiment, Arnold was in hearty agreement. 对于最后一个观点，阿诺德强烈赞同。 

4. heartily ADV 强烈地 

例： Most Afghans are heartily sick of war. 大多数阿富汗人极其厌恶战争。 

5. ADJ A hearty meal is large and very satisfying. (饭菜) 丰盛的 

例： The men ate a hearty breakfast. 男士们吃了一顿丰盛的早餐。 

6. heartily ADV 胃口很大地 [ADV after v] 

例： He ate heartily but would drink only beer. 他吃饭的胃口很大，但只喝啤酒。

</div>

